---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Field Rules | Dear Bug Diary">
  <article>
    <p class="eyebrow">Field rules</p>
    <h1>Bugsy's field rules</h1>
    <p>Small rules for staying useful, skeptical, and kind to future testers.</p>
  </article>

  <ul class="rule-list">
    <li>Never trust a bug just because it says it is fixed.</li>
    <li>A green pipeline is good news, not proof that all risks are gone.</li>
    <li>A closed bug becomes useful only when it turns into a reusable regression check.</li>
    <li>Evidence is the difference between "probably fine" and "release-ready."</li>
    <li>Flaky tests are tiny chaos machines wearing automation badges.</li>
    <li>Human review is still required when the risk is domain-specific, visual, or ambiguous.</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
